---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} articleSchema={{headline: pageTitle, description: pageDescription, datePublished: '2026-05', authorName: 'Toolwise Team'}} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>OBS Studio Complete Guide: How to Record Your Screen for Free in 2026</h1>
			<p>OBS Studio is the most powerful free screen recorder and live streaming software. This guide covers everything from installation to your first recording.</p>

			<h2>What is OBS Studio?</h2>
			<p>OBS Studio (Open Broadcaster Software) is a free, open-source tool for video recording and live streaming. It's used by YouTubers, Twitch streamers, educators, and professionals worldwide.</p>

			<h2>Quick Setup Guide</h2>
			<ol>
				<li><strong>Download:</strong> Get OBS from obsproject.com (Windows, Mac, Linux)</li>
				<li><strong>Install:</strong> Run the installer and follow prompts</li>
				<li><strong>Add Source:</strong> Click "+" under Sources → Select "Display Capture" or "Window Capture"</li>
				<li><strong>Adjust Settings:</strong> Go to Settings → Output → Set recording format to MP4</li>
				<li><strong>Start Recording:</strong> Click "Start Recording" button</li>
			</ol>

			<h2>Key Features</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Unlimited scenes and sources</li>
				<li>Multiple audio tracks</li>
				<li>Real-time audio/video mixing</li>
				<li>Custom transitions and filters</li>
				<li>Stream to YouTube, Twitch, Facebook simultaneously</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Best Settings for Recording</h2>
			<table>
				<tr><th>Setting</th><th>Recommendation</th></tr>
				<tr><td>Resolution</td><td>1920x1080 (1080p)</td></tr>
				<tr><td>FPS</td><td>30 for tutorials, 60 for gaming</td></tr>
				<tr><td>Encoder</td><td>x264 (CPU) or NVENC (NVIDIA GPU)</td></tr>
				<tr><td>Bitrate</td><td>4000-6000 Kbps for 1080p</td></tr>
				<tr><td>Format</td><td>MP4 (or MKV to prevent corruption)</td></tr>
			</table>

			<h2>Pros and Cons</h2>
			<h3>Pros</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Completely free and open source</li>
				<li>No watermark or time limits</li>
				<li>Professional-grade features</li>
				<li>Active community and plugins</li>
			</ul>
			<h3>Cons</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Steep learning curve for beginners</li>
				<li>Can be resource-intensive on older computers</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Who Should Use OBS?</h2>
			<p><strong>Best for:</strong> YouTubers, Twitch streamers, online course creators, gamers, and anyone who needs professional screen recording without paying.</p>

			<h2>FAQ</h2>
			<p><strong>Q: Is OBS Studio really free?</strong><br>A: Yes. OBS is 100% free and open source. No hidden fees, no watermarks.</p>
			<p><strong>Q: Can I use OBS on Mac?</strong><br>A: Yes. OBS works on Windows, Mac, and Linux.</p>
			<p><strong>Q: Why is my recording laggy?</strong><br>A: Lower your resolution/FPS or switch to hardware encoding (NVENC/AMF) if you have a dedicated GPU.</p>

